ring in fish or vegetable soups.","Sunflower oil or similar neutrally flavoured oil can be used instead of grapeseed oil.","Fresh, peeled and roughly chopped tomatoes (approx. <b>12 ripe<b> Roma tomatoes) can be substituted for homemade or shop-bought passata. The fresh tomatoes do not need to be puréed as they will break down during cooking.","The cooking time can be further extended to make the kasoundi thicker."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","2h","1"]}